#### § 40.191 What is a refusal to take a DOT drug test, and what are the consequences?

(a) As an employee, you have refused to take a drug test if you:

(1) Fail to appear for any test (except a pre-employment test) within a reasonable time, as determined by the employer, consistent with applicable DOT agency regulations, after being directed to do so by the employer. This includes the failure of an employee (including an owner-operator) to appear for a test when called by a C/TPA (see [§ 40.61(a)](/current/title-49/section-40.61#p-40.61\(a\)));

(2) Fail to remain at the testing site until the testing process is complete. Provided that an employee who leaves the collection site before the testing process commences (_see_ [§ 40.63(c)](/current/title-49/section-40.63#p-40.63\(c\)) or [§ 40.72(d)(3)](/current/title-49/section-40.72#p-40.72\(d\)\(3\)), as applicable) for a pre-employment test is not deemed to have refused to test. The collector is not required to inform an employee that the failure to remain at the collection site is a refusal. If an employee leaves prior to the completion of the testing process, per [§ 40.355(i)](/current/title-49/section-40.355#p-40.355\(i\)) the employer must decide whether the employee's actions constitute a refusal;

(3) Fail to provide a specimen for any drug test required by this part or DOT agency regulations. Provided that an employee who does not provide a specimen because he or she has left the testing site befo

red by this part or DOT agency regulations. Provided that an employee who does not provide a specimen because he or she has left the testing site before the testing process commences (_see_ [§ 40.63(c)](/current/title-49/section-40.63#p-40.63\(c\)) or [§ 40.72(d)(3)](/current/title-49/section-40.72#p-40.72\(d\)\(3\)), as applicable) for a pre-employment test is not deemed to have refused to test. The collector is not required to inform an employee that the failure to remain at the collection site is a refusal. If an employee leaves prior to the completion of the testing process, per [§ 40.355(i)](/current/title-49/section-40.355#p-40.355\(i\)) the employer must decide whether the employee's actions constitute a refusal;

(4) In the case of a directly observed or monitored urine collection in a drug test, fail to permit the observation or monitoring of an employee's provision of a specimen (_see_ [§§ 40.67(m)](/current/title-49/section-40.67#p-40.67\(m\)) and [40.69(g)](/current/title-49/section-40.69#p-40.69\(g\)));

